name: Laboratory in Neuroscience
description: A laboratory course based on current research techniques for students in the Neuroscience Specialist and Major programs. Lab topics may include human brain imaging and disorders; animal behaviour, electrophysiology and cell culture; and microarray analysis of neural development. (Lab Materials Fee: $50)
prerequisites: 9 FCE complete, HMB200H1/HMB220H1/PSY290H1, HMB265H1/BIO260H1, BIO230H1/ BIO255H1
